View and Set the Accumulated Dose Rate

Viewing The Set Point

  • Depress and hold the ALARM button and then press the DOSE button.
  • Next, release both buttons, and the display will flash the set point value for the Dose Alarm.
  • The unit will return to displaying the Rate in about 10 seconds if no further actions are performed.

Change the Dose Alarm Set Point

  • With the unit in Rate mode, press and hold the ALARM button and then press the DOSE button.
  • Release both buttons and the display will flash the set point value for the Dose Alarm.
  • Within 10 seconds, press and release the CLR/TEST button.
  • Repeatedly press and release the DOSE button until the desired unit (µGy, cGy, or Gy) and decimal point location are displayed.
  • Press and release the CLR/TEST button to lock the Unit and Decimal Point location selected. The left-most digit will flash (blink).
  • Repeatedly press and release the DOSE button until the desired left-most digit is displayed.
  • Press and release the CLR/TEST button to lock in the left-most digit. The center digit will flash (blink).
  • Repeatedly press and release the DOSE button until the desired center digit is displayed.
  • Press and release the CLR/TEST button to lock in the center digit. The right-most digit will flash (blink).
  • Repeatedly press and release the DOSE button until the desired right-most digit is displayed.
  • Press and release the CLR/TEST button to lock in the right digit.
  • The UDR-14 will display the Dose Alarm setting for approximately 10 seconds.
  • To return to the Rate mode, press and release the RATE button.
